Even though we fought like this sometimes... we always made up quickly.

Life in the kingdom was better than when I was an orphan, as I could live a
normal life, but there was always discrimination based on birth, and
honestly, whether I advanced in rank or not didn't matter to me.

I'm sure many of the nobles are pleased with the current situation, with me
not being around.
Umi "Grandma... Are you not feeling well...?"

Umi's Mother "What are you talking about? Grandma is always energetic,
right?"
Umi "No way! Grandma is always in bed!"

Grandma "I stay here because I like it. But I'm sorry, Umi... You want to
play outside with Grandma, don't you?"

Umi "I want to play, but... Umi is okay! I'll go pray for Grandma to get
better soon!"
Umi's Mother "Thank you... Umi..."
Umi "Toto, welcome back!"
Umi's Father "Hey Umi. Are you going somewhere?"

Umi "Yes. I'm going to pray to the god Kureshiresama for Grandma's illness
to be cured."

Umi's Father "Kureshirei-sama, huh. Oh, that's very good of you, Umi! If
you pray, I'm sure she'll get better."

Umi "That's not true... I've been praying all the time, but Grandma isn't
getting any better."
Umi's Mother "Dear, welcome back."

Umi's Father "Ah, I'm back... Sorry, I searched all over the forest, but I
couldn't find any grapes."

Umi "Grandma... used to love grapes... Maybe she could get better if she
could eat some..."
